    "summary": "Sometimes your body does what it wants to do and not what you want it to do! You meet hard to place physical / emotional challenges. That is what I work on and have helped many people with. \n\nI use a mix of old Eastern more 'energetic methods' and up to date Western therapeutic approaches such as Focusing and Somatic Experiencing. I always work with how you relate to your body. I interact with people mostly with just words. Touch helps in some cases. I get good results even by telephone or Skype over long distances. I use Dutch, English or French. \n\nI used to be scientist with a career in the Netherlands and the USA (Massachusetts Institute of Technology). Later I became a business consultant for strategy in Europe.\n \nAfter I \"retired\" I moved to Thailand to study and practice Taoism with Master Mantak Chia. I became a senior instructor for Chi Kung and a teacher and practitioner of Chi Nei Tsang and Energy Healing. I liked the holistic approach of body AND emotions. In my therapy I incorporated these methods with up to date Western methods such as focusing - to connect with the wisdom of your body - and somatic experiencing - for trauma resolution.\nAt present I am mostly in the Hague, in the Netherlands, but also regularly in Paris and the Boston area in the USA.Yet, I can work anywhere by telephone or Skype.\n\nSpecialties: Psycho-Somatic work, Trauma Resolution, Regression-therapy, Game of Transformation, Chi Kung, Chi Nei Tsang (Chinese energetic massage), Advaita Vedanta",
