                            "day": null,
                            "year": 2011
                        }
                    },
                    "company": "independent therapist",
                    "description": "I used to work with a Chinese form of massage Chi Nei Tsang which in and by itself is very psycho-somatic. In most cases I found that people who came to me had other problems which had nestled in their body. I would steer our discussion in an appropriate direction and at the same time do some massage. That worked fine. So I later trained in Somatic Experiencing to be better able to deal with trauma and in Focusing so that I could also teach people how to communicate better with what they felt in their bodies. Now I live in Finland mostly and my work goes via Skype or telephone.",
